Ask HN: If you could reimagine your email inbox, what would you pick?
text:
I can think of things like

1. built-in mail merge and updatable contacts where someone can directly reply to your mail-merged email and unsubscribe

2. shareable urls of emails - I hate that I can only forward/cc people to share an email with people. Shareable emails will make bookmarking important emails in the browser MUCH easier

3. sidebar comments/discussions section built into the email inbox instead of unending chains of reply/reply-alls.

Anything else that could make the email inbox more interesting?

Show HN: Top Quant/Algotrading Githubs Automated
text:
With a seed project defining the audience, determines their most popular Githubs.

Interesting results! [1]

One journalist was surprised [2] on the Quant and Algotrading results.

Github's Rest API [3] is actually quite complex - and has undocumented hurdles. E.g. when there's more than 40K stars the API caps it there - unless you use the GraphQL API... [4]

There's a lot more meat on the Github bones. Stay tuned.

[1] https://profitview.net/blog/open-source-trading-projects

[2] https://www.efinancialcareers.com/news/2022/07/coding-langua...

[3] https://docs.github.com/en/rest

[4] https://docs.github.com/en/graphql
